    <prj:ScienceGoal mode="Other">
        <prj:name>Determination of binary parameters for a symbiotic star R Aquarii</prj:name>
        <prj:note>The purpose of this observation is to resolve the binary components in R Aqr.

The radio continuum for the WD is expected to originate the HII region with a peck flux of about 1 mJy as a minimum. Even in minimum expected WD flux, only 3 min (total 30 min) observation acheive the SNR 10. 

In our expectation with the present study, the separation of two components is about 8.21 mas with the P.A. of 54 deg in Oct. 2015. 
The relative positional accurancy between the two component is given by ~0.5 x synthesised beam/SNR. The maximum synthesised beam of ALMA is about 32 mas, then, the relative positional accurancy can acheive less than 1 mas (0.5 mas)</prj:note>
