        </prj:TechnicalJustification>
        <prj:TechnicalJustification>
            <prj:justificationText>For the purpose, we need the highest angular resolution of ~30 mas in cycle 3 ALMA observation. ACA observation is not requried. </prj:justificationText>
            <prj:justificationKey>ED_ANGULAR_RESOLUTION</prj:justificationKey>
        </prj:TechnicalJustification>
        <prj:TechnicalJustification>
            <prj:justificationText>In order to achieve the science purpose, the minimum required sensitivity is more than 4  times S/N ratio.
Expected peak flux density for the white dwarf companion is more than 1 mJy in band 6. Then, requried RMS is less than 250 uJy over the frequency band. Since the minimum on source integration time is 2 min, we can acheive the RMS of 125 uJy with 8 times S/N ration for the sensitivity. 
Moreover, higher S/N ratio can be obtained a higher positional accurancy, so that we request the RMS is less than 100 uJy for the 10 times S/N ratio.</prj:justificationText>
            <prj:justificationKey>ED_SENSITIVITY</prj:justificationKey>
        </prj:TechnicalJustification>
        <prj:TechnicalJustification>
            <prj:justificationText>This observation is not required a polarisation observation.</prj:justificationText>
            <prj:justificationKey>ED_SINGLE_POLARISATION</prj:justificationKey>
