    <prp:abstract>We propose to carry out the continuum observation towards a symbiotic star R Aqr with ALMA. In AGB binaries, the companion has a strong influence on the binary evolution into various shape of planetary nebulae, and varitey of astronomical processes such as an accretion disk, collimating jet-like features, nova outbursts, and a spiral structure of circumstellar envelopes. However, the detail processes and mechanisms are not well known. To find out a precise binary parameters present important implications and constraints for understanding a late stage of stellar evolution, and binary phenomena.
R Aqr is a one of well-known symbiotic stars composed of a Mira variable and a white dwarf. In order to determine binary parameters, we have been performing astrometric monitor observations for the Mira variable with VERA (VLBI Exploration of Radio Astrometry). Combining radial velocity and astrometry data, we found probable binary parameters.
The proposed ALMA observation with the highest resolution and sensitivity will provide crucial information of relative positions of components for determining the most reliable binary parameters to understand the nature of R Aqr and relative objects. </prp:abstract>
